Prof. Charles Soludo has announced the appointment of three persons into his administration. The appointment is coming less than six hours after his inauguration as the sixth Governor of Anambra State. He was inaugurated as Governor on Thursday. The statement containing the new appointments was released to newsmen by Mr Joe Anatune, on Thursday in Awka. The statement announced the appointment of Prof. Osita Chukwulobelu as Secretary to the State Government (SSG) and Dr Chukwudi Okoli as the Accountant General, while Mr Chinedu Nwoye was appointed as Deputy Chief Of Staff/State Chief of Protocol. â€”